# epic-harness Quality Skills

Core skill rules applied automatically throughout every session.

---

## TDD — Test-Driven Development

**Always write a failing test before any implementation.**

Red → Green → Refactor. One behavior per cycle.

- Test name reads like a spec: `it("returns 401 when token is expired")`
- Run test — confirm it fails for the right reason (Red)
- Write minimum code to pass (Green)
- Refactor without changing behavior, rerun tests (Refactor)

Anti-patterns to reject:
- "I'll add tests later" — write the test NOW
- "This is too simple to test" — if it has a return value, it's testable
- Writing implementation before any test exists

Evidence required before claiming done:
- [ ] Failing test output shown (Red)
- [ ] Passing test output shown (Green)
- [ ] Test covers behavior, not implementation details

