## Secure — Security Review

**Apply when touching auth, database, API endpoints, secrets, or user input.**

Checklist (mark each ✓ or N/A):
- [ ] All user input sanitized before use in queries
- [ ] Parameterized queries used — no string-concatenated SQL
- [ ] No `eval()`, `exec()`, or template injection vectors
- [ ] Auth checks on every protected endpoint
- [ ] No hardcoded credentials or secrets in code
- [ ] Sensitive data not logged (passwords, tokens, PII)
- [ ] `.env` files in `.gitignore`
- [ ] RBAC/permissions checked before data access

Anti-patterns to reject:
- Storing secrets in committed config files
- "We'll harden it before production"
- Internal API = trusted (it is not)

